--- USER ---
cant test it yet so lets discuss how add assets to the game. what files are more
useful for a tiles background? png, svg, with alpha, size, etc? guide me

--- ASSISTANT ---
For tile backgrounds, a 256×256 RGBA PNG is ideal. PNG gives lossless quality,
alpha channel lets transparent corners blend naturally when clipped to hex shape,
and 256px is large enough to look sharp at typical zoom levels without being
wasteful. SVG is tempting but rasterizing it per-frame on canvas is slower than
a pre-decoded bitmap. Keep file size under ~100KB per texture. A repeating
seamless tile is a bonus but not required since we clip to hex anyway.

